 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.2.3.2","title":"[STUB][B3][build] Route browser-core wasm-pack cargo through rch and preserve consumer build contract","description":"Sibling child under asupersync-v2ofj7.2.3. The workspace build path currently reaches browser-core via scripts/build_browser_core_artifacts.sh, which invokes wasm-pack build without the repo-standard rch-routed cargo wrapper already used by scripts/validate_rust_browser_consumer.sh. Make the canonical browser-core build path use the same rch wrapper pattern, add non-overlapping regression coverage in the Rust-browser consumer contract surface, and validate with the build script plus targeted rch-backed cargo tests. Avoid browser-core tarball truthfulness/package-files edits owned by asupersync-v2ofj7.2.3.1.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"VioletMill","created_at":"2026-04-03T16:46:07.415310031Z","created_by":"VioletMill","updated_at":"2026-04-03T16:46:07.415310031Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["browser","build","packaging","rch","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.2.3.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.2.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T16:46:07.415310031Z","created_by":"VioletMill","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.2.4","title":"[STUB][B4] Align WASM disposition docs and audit records with retained scaffold truth","description":"## Background
Track B no longer has the exact state recorded in `docs/stub_disposition_matrix.md`: the matrix still says `asupersync-wasm/src/{exports.rs,error.rs,types.rs}` are comment-only placeholders, but the surviving `asupersync-wasm` crate now contains retained scaffold / fail-closed code that is intentionally non-canonical next to `asupersync-browser-core`. There are also no audit records for the retained scaffold files.

## Scope
- Update Track B closeout docs so they describe the current honest role of `asupersync-wasm`.
- Add audit-index coverage for the retained scaffold files after a fresh read.
- Keep the wording aligned with the canonical-owner decision from B1/B2 without claiming packaging validation that belongs to B3.

## Deliverables
- Truthful `docs/stub_disposition_matrix.md` language for Surface 1.
- `audit_index.jsonl` entries for the audited `asupersync-wasm` retained scaffold files.
- Notes that clearly distinguish canonical owner (`asupersync-browser-core`) from retained non-canonical scaffold.

## Validation
- Focused read of the relevant `asupersync-wasm` files plus consistency check against README and existing stub-resolution probes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"OliveDeer","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-04-03T20:32:13.705038822Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T20:34:25.883681400Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T20:34:25.883155563Z","close_reason":"Completed: aligned Track B Surface 1 docs with retained-scaffold truth and added audit records for asupersync-wasm files","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","docs","stub","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.2.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-03T20:32:13.705038822Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-v2ofj7.3","title":"[STUB][Track C] Macro surface contract totalization","description":"## Background
Asupersync already supports proc-macro-based `scope!`, `spawn!`, `join!`, and `race!`, but the audited surface still contains permanently broken macro exports (`try_join!`, `quorum!`) and needs a clean statement of what the supported macro contract actually is in proc-macro and no-proc-macro builds.

## Scope
- Freeze the supported macro set.
- Resolve exported placeholder macros.
- Align remaining fallback/docs/re-exports with the chosen contract.

## Why this matters
A public macro that exists only to fail at expansion time is documentation debt baked into the API surface.","acceptance_criteria":"1. The supported macro surface is explicit across proc-macro-enabled and proc-macro-disabled builds.
2. `try_join!` and `quorum!` no longer exist as permanent placeholders.
3. `join!` / `race!` fallback behavior, re-exports, and docs match reality.","notes":"This track reuses the existing `try_join!` and `quorum!` beads rather than replacing them, but their framing is updated from "probably delete" to "resolve according to the macro contract decision bead".

Validation charter:
